---
import Tool from '../../layouts/Tool.astro';
---

<Tool
	title="Image to PDF Converter – JPG PNG WEBP to PDF | SinzTools"
	description="Convert images to PDF online for free. Convert JPG, PNG, WEBP to PDF instantly in your browser. No upload required - works locally on your device."
	tool="image-to-pdf"
>
<a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>
<h1>Image to PDF Converter</h1>
<p>Convert your images (JPG, PNG, WEBP) to a single PDF document instantly in your browser. Perfect for creating documents from photos, combining multiple images, or preparing files for printing.</p>

<div class="privacy-note">
	<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" class="icon">
		<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75 11.25 15 15 9.75m-3-7.036A11.959 11.959 0 0 1 3.598 6 11.99 11.99 0 0 0 3 9.749c0 5.592 3.824 10.29 9 11.623 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.623 0-1.31-.21-2.571-.598-3.751h-.152c-3.196 0-6.1-1.248-8.25-3.285Z"/>
	</svg>
	Runs locally — no uploads. Your files never leave your device.
</div>

<h2>How to Use</h2>
<p>Select multiple images, arrange them in order, choose your PDF settings, and click "Convert to PDF". Your PDF will be ready for download.</p>

<div class="drop-zone" id="dropZone">
	<input type="file" id="fileInput" accept="image/png,image/jpeg,image/webp" multiple required style="display: none;">
	<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" class="icon">
		<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 16.5V9.75m0 0 3 3m-3-3-3 3M6.75 19.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-1.41-8.775 5.25 5.25 0 0 1 10.233-2.33 3 3 0 0 1 3.758 3.848A3.752 3.752 0 0 1 18 19.5H6.75Z"/>
	</svg>
	<p>Drop images here or <label for="fileInput">browse</label></p>
	<small>Supports JPG, PNG, WEBP • Multiple files allowed</small>
</div>

<div id="imageList" class="image-list" style="display: none;">
	<h3>Images to Convert (<span id="imageCount">0</span>)</h3>
	<div id="thumbnails" class="thumbnails"></div>
</div>

<div class="options-section">
	<h3>PDF Options</h3>
	<div class="option-group">
		<label for="pageSize">Page Size:</label>
		<select id="pageSize">
			<option value="A4">A4</option>
			<option value="LETTER">Letter</option>
			<option value="FIT">Fit image to page</option>
		</select>
	</div>

	<div class="option-group">
		<label for="orientation">Orientation:</label>
		<select id="orientation">
			<option value="AUTO">Auto</option>
			<option value="PORTRAIT">Portrait</option>
			<option value="LANDSCAPE">Landscape</option>
		</select>
	</div>

	<div class="option-group">
		<label for="margin">Margin:</label>
		<select id="margin">
			<option value="SMALL">Small</option>
			<option value="NONE">None</option>
		</select>
	</div>
</div>

<button type="button" id="convertBtn">Convert to PDF</button>

<div class="loading" id="loading">
	<div class="spinner"></div>
	<p>Converting images to PDF... This may take a moment.</p>
</div>

<div id="errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>
<div id="output"></div>

<h2>How this Image to PDF Converter works</h2>
<p>This tool uses your browser's built-in canvas technology and PDF generation libraries to convert images to PDF. All processing happens locally in your browser - your images never leave your device, ensuring complete privacy and security.</p>

<h2>Supported formats & features</h2>
<p>We support JPG, PNG, and WEBP image formats. You can convert multiple images into a single PDF document, arrange them in any order, and customize page size, orientation, and margins for optimal results.</p>
</Tool>
